A film critic is conducting a research to analyze the popularity of visual media vs traditional art forms. He collected data for a period of 12 months. The data represents the number of people who visited art galleries and those who watched movies in theaters each month. The data is as follows:

Art Galleries: {500, 600, 550, 700, 650, 600, 750, 800, 700, 850, 900, 950}
Movie Theaters: {1000, 1100, 1200, 1300, 1400, 1500, 1600, 1700, 1800, 1900, 2000, 2100}

The critic wants to predict the number of people who will visit art galleries and watch movies in theaters in the next month. He believes that the popularity of both forms is increasing linearly over time. 

Using the method of least squares, determine the equations of the line of best fit for both data sets. Use these equations to predict the number of visitors for both art galleries and movie theaters for the 13th month.
